Windows Registry Editor Version 5.00

; Turn AutoPlay Off

; When the Shell detects the insertion of new media or the attachment of a hot-plug device, the contents of the device or media are determined, then Autoplay takes over prompting the user or automatically executing an option.


; Sources 

; https://www.majorgeeks.com/content/page/turn_autoplay_on_or_off.html

[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\AutoplayHandlers]
"DisableAutoplay"=dword:00000001 